goals.rationale: A box plot can show the distribution of yield across all sites and help identify any outliers or differences in yield between sites.

goals.question: How does the yield of different barley varieties compare?
goals.visualization: bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A bar chart can show the yield of each variety and help identify which varieties have the highest and lowest yields.

goals.question: What is the trend in yield over time?
goals.visualization: line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: A line chart can show the trend in yield over time and help identify any patterns or changes in yield from year to year.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield at each site?
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the distribution of yield at each site and help identify any differences in yield between sites.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between yield and location?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by location
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and location and help identify any correlation between the two variables.

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.boxplot(x="yield", data=data, color='skyblue')
    ax.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Yield of Barley in Bushels per Acre')
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.barplot(x="variety", y="yield", data=data, ci=None)
    chart.axhline(y=data['yield'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Mean Yield')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    chart.set(xlabel='Variety', ylabel='Yield (bushels per acre)')
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('How does the yield of different barley varieties compare?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='yield', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend in yield over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data[['yield', 'site']]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='yield', hue='site', multiple='stack', kde=True, element='step', alpha=0.5, palette='bright')
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Yield: {:.2f}'.format(data['yield'].mean()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield at each site?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
